726590f-c.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Seneca Avenue
726590f-c.text:
1410 Flushing Avenue, at the S. E. corner of Seneca Avenue,
showing the Covert-Jenkins House, built about 1785. John G. Jenkins
Sr. bought the property in 1864. For additional data see the ''New
York Sun,'' February 18, 1939.

726581f-c.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Seneca Avenue
726581f-c.text:
1410 Flushing Avenue, at the S. E. corner of Seneca Avenue,
showing the Covert-Jenkins Farmhouse and barns, viewing northeast-
ward across cultivated land on Seneca Avenue. In the center back-
ground of the view is the Nicholas Wyckoff House, on the north
side of Flushing Avenue. For additional data see the ''New York
Sun,'' February 18, 1939.
View 1: 1922
View 2: 1923
Views 3,4: 1929
